The Telegraph - Calcutta

 Meet begins today

Pune: Top stars from the continent are participating in the Asian billiards championship commencing here Sunday. 

Nineteen cueists from Asia, including the hosts, will vie for top honours in the tournament carrying prize money of over Rs 3 lakh, president of Billiards and Snooker Association of Maharashtra (BSAM), Michael Ferreira said here Saturday. 

Players from Pakistan, South Korea, Sri Lanka, Thailand, Myanmar and Singapore are taking part in the championship which will be played on 100-up, best of five-frame format, he said adding, the Indian challenge will be spearheaded by defending champion Devendra Joshi. 

 (PTI) 




